website_summaries.verdict: This nail lacquer has some excellent features such as the protein-rich formula and natural results, but also has limited colors and possible application issues.
pros: Brand focuses on natural nail care
Polish is formulated with protein, which may provide added strength to nails
Dries quickly and wears well under most typical circumstances
A brand that is used by many salons
cons: Streaking and bubbling during application are common

customer_reviews.title: Very satisfied
customer_reviews.text: Great as a strengthening coat, even better with color! Color is very pigmented with full coverage in 2 coats. Minimal chipping. Comparable quality to my other favorite brand Zoya but with the added benefit of Nailtique peptides to keep my nails strong. Love it! The only problem is the limited number of color to choose from. Hope Nailtique can expand its color selection.
customer_reviews.author: Cen

customer_reviews.title: and I'm good to go for several days
customer_reviews.text: The Moscow red is a true (blue tone) red that looks fabulous. I find that it lasts up to a full week. I've had it on for five days without any chips! I have thin nails, but after using nailtiques formula 2 they are much firmer and stronger. I put on Nailtiques forumla 1 along this color polish and a quick dry top coat, and I'm good to go for several days! Yes, it's a bit thick, but I think that's part of the beauty if you have thin nails like me. It really wasn't hard to work with. Thanks for the color polish, Nailtiques! :-)
customer_reviews.author: Rene Smith

customer_reviews.title: Clean subtle color and protection
customer_reviews.text: I use several Nailtiques products for brittle dry nails. This color gives me just enough coverage to look manicured but doesn’t show nicks. It’s is compatible with my other Nailtiques products.
customer_reviews.author: MD

customer_reviews.title: Healed Nails-Nice Colors
customer_reviews.text: I was an OPI devotee for years, but when my nails cratered after a few months of gel, I could not get them to heal. My daughter got me the Protein treatment (step 2 or something) for Christmas. After six months of treatment, I finally had nails that were not splitting and peeling. Because the protein is so effective, I wanted to continue that with the Nailtiques protein color. Would be nice if there were more colors available, but I am loving the colors I got and the protection for my nails.
customer_reviews.author: Ctm

customer_reviews.title: Looks cheap
customer_reviews.text: Bought this for my wife. She was looking for a white nail polish. This is more like a silver color, and doesn't give an even coat. It looks like cheap streaks of paint when you apply it. Couldn't return it according to the seller. Waste of money.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Too thick even with the first coat!
customer_reviews.text: I love Nailtiques and have been using it for years. Love their protein formulas and usually their nail colors but this one is horrible. Went on way to thick even as a first coat. Second coat resulted in dents and marks on my nails. I have never had a problem before with their nail polishes but this one sucks!
customer_reviews.author: S. McPherson

customer_reviews.title: Great polish that lasts
customer_reviews.text: I do wish Nailtiques would come out with more modern colors because I love the polish with the Nail Protein 2 Plus. I have never had long strong nails in my life until I commited to the Nailtiques Protein 2 Plus for 6 weeks then started adding the colors. Two coats of 2 Plus, followed by 2 coats of color, followed by one coat of Protein 2 Plus every other day and the polish lasts a full two weeks. My nails look better then ever, but the colors are a bit boring. I've tried other polishes and they always bubble with the Protein 2 Plus as the base coat.
customer_reviews.author: trimommy2009

customer_reviews.title: Beautiful Color
customer_reviews.text: This lacquer is so thin and streaky that I can't see the benefit to using it at all. ..tossing it in the bin.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: My nails look amazing and are super strong!
customer_reviews.text: This has really changed my nails. They look great and people always ask if I just got a manicure.
customer_reviews.author: Happy

customer_reviews.title: Shimmer! You can't tell.
customer_reviews.text: Although I love their products this color does not appear correctly. You can not tell that this is a shimmer not a solid color.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Nailtiques Protein Nail Lacquer
customer_reviews.text: Really appreciate the protein in the Nailtiques products, always a plus for my dry brittle nails and the colors are current with a quality nail brush for easy application.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Arrived dried up
customer_reviews.text: The color is nice. The staying power is OK too. But it arrived dried out so I could not use it. Fortunately I had already purchased Formula Fix kit from Nailtiques to dilute their Protein formula. So I used it to save this nail polish.
customer_reviews.author: AK

customer_reviews.title: color is perfect for a well manicured look
customer_reviews.text: This is a great polish and the color is perfect for a well manicured look or to use with french manicure. Love, love, love it!
customer_reviews.author: Michelle Blackledge

customer_reviews.title: An okay product
customer_reviews.text: Color is very light. Polish flakes off easily but suppose that is necessary if the protein product is to get under it.

customer_reviews.title: I love that this lacquer is made with the same nail-strengthening ...
customer_reviews.text: Goes on smooth, stays on for a week or more! I love that this lacquer is made with the same nail-strengthening proteins as the Nailtiques Formula 2...I use them together and my formerly thin, peeling nails are stronger than they've ever been. Highly recommended.
customer_reviews.author: Elizabeth E.

customer_reviews.title: San Tropez is translucent
customer_reviews.text: This didn't look any different on my nails than using the regular Nailtique treatment polishes. I've used and trusted Nailtiques treatments for years, so this was a real disappointment.
customer_reviews.author: foster

customer_reviews.title: One Star
customer_reviews.text: it takes for ever to dry and it chips off really quick.
customer_reviews.author: Jen

customer_reviews.title: exellent service, order came  very fast
customer_reviews.text: I like this lacquer,looks very,very good on my nails and last 2 times longer than regular polish.

customer_reviews.title: It applied very nicely. Took too long to dry and smugged easily
customer_reviews.text: It applied very nicely. Took too long to dry and smugged easily. Did last more than a week before coming off.
customer_reviews.author: Joanne Barbier

customer_reviews.title: protein nail polish
customer_reviews.text: this is one of the best nail products ever. they help my dry and brittle nails stay very strong and even helps it grow faster.

customer_reviews.title: All of the Nailtiques products have helped my nail get ...
customer_reviews.text: All of the Nailtiques products have helped my nail get back in shape after taking of years of Fake nails

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: The best nail polish.lasts about 1 week and 1/2 .love it. No chipping whatsoever
customer_reviews.author: Katherine Palacios

customer_reviews.title: Wrong Color!
customer_reviews.text: I was excited to try Nailtiques' new-to-me polish with protein, as I'm trying to rebuild my nails after acrylics. However, the color here--which looks like a nice deep red--is nothing like the one I received: a bright red color only seen on ladies of the evening. Thankfully, Amazon was great--as usual--and refunded the money. I highly recommend the company changing the picture to reflect a bright, harsh red--if that's what people are looking for. I've worn polish for years and have *never* seen this shade of red on anyone. Ever.
customer_reviews.author: Teachah Lady

customer_reviews.title: Great color
customer_reviews.text: I love Nailtiques products, I have been using nail protein for years and love their nail polish. This polish and color wears well with anything.
customer_reviews.author: Super Aunt

customer_reviews.title: happy with this product
customer_reviews.text: This product was packed super well and was in perfect condition on arrival. It was more pale & sheer then I expected. One coat is barely visible. However I don't like color on my hands and using this - it gives a subtle blur effect and it makes my manicure last 3x as long as the Nailtiques treatment alone, Two coats on my toes - is OK. But hard to get the color even. Still its better than other brands I've tried. I've just ordered Cairo color and can't wait to find out how that works.
customer_reviews.author: S. Ahola

customer_reviews.title: It's red alright
customer_reviews.text: This was my first Nailtiques color polish and I can't say that I was impressed. I thought the consistency would be like the nail proteins with color, but they are thicker and do not dry as fast. The color is a nice rich red, but I think I'll just stick to the clear protein since my nails look nice enough with no color now. I was just curious.
customer_reviews.author: Amyzgr8

customer_reviews.title: The bottle lid was not tight. It leaked in ...
customer_reviews.text: The bottle lid was not tight. It leaked in the package and I coul smell the product throught the package.
customer_reviews.author: prissyj

customer_reviews.title: This nail polish s really great. Once my nails healed enough to wear a ...
customer_reviews.text: This nail polish s really great. Once my nails healed enough to wear a lacquer I tried OPI and experienced a big set back. The nailtiques lacquer word really well and don't cause setbacks. This is a pretty color but for the most art Nailtiques colors are disappointing. I'm planning to stick with it because I really love wearing nail lacquer. I use one coat of Formula 2 Plus. Then 2 coats of color and 1 coat of 2 Plus as a top coat.
customer_reviews.author: JDH

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: it has helped my nail after been on gel and acrylic for 12 years
customer_reviews.author: DINORAH FRAGA

customer_reviews.title: Three Stars
customer_reviews.text: Love the polish, but unsatisfied that every time I have ordered polish it has always spilled in the box
customer_reviews.author: Enthusiastic Reader

customer_reviews.title: great color!!
customer_reviews.text: This polish was just the right kind of pink I was looking for!! I love it .. its a great color and it last very well..
customer_reviews.author: vicmer

customer_reviews.title: Great color that also strengthens your nails!
customer_reviews.text: I love Nailtiques!! I found the shimmery white color a couple of years ago, and it has been my go-to ever since. Not only does it help your nails grow, but it was also a wonderful neutral nail color. This color doesn't disappoint! It is a great deep red. Perfect for all my upcoming holiday parties!
customer_reviews.author: Kristin D.

customer_reviews.title: For a great manicure
customer_reviews.text: Works perfectly with Nailtques Formula 2 to give me a full week's manicure. This is a lovely light pink. I apply 1 coat of Formula 2, 2 coats of color and then seal with a 2nd coat of Formula2. I do need to apply a new coat of Formula2 every day.
customer_reviews.author: sdbev

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: Nice polish with protein - stays for a week too!
customer_reviews.author: Bosco

customer_reviews.title: Wouldn't recommend
customer_reviews.text: The polish color is very pretty but when I received it, it had dried pink bubbles coming out of the top before I ever opened the bottle and the polish was very thick as if it were old. I had to throw it out. It could have just been a bad batch but I won't order it again.
customer_reviews.author: LisaL

customer_reviews.title: Would pay twice as much.
customer_reviews.text: I am a Nail Tech and have seem many products. I have used Nailtiques for over 20 years, and as a result have great naails. I just got the polish and have fell in love again. It's tough as nails doesn't chip and one coat covers. No need for two. Great stuff. Would buy it at twice the price.
customer_reviews.author: MariestherLove Robbins

customer_reviews.title: #1 in Perfection Department
customer_reviews.text: I committed to Nailtique products over a year ago. I went from splitting, peeling, breaking nails to a set of ten that look and feel so perfect, everyone just assumes they're fake. I bought a few of these colors and along with the protein formula as a base and top coat, I am on day 15 without a chip. There's just no other product like this on the market. This color is a bright pink, very pretty on short nails, might be a bit much on long ones. The bottles are small but a little goes a long way since they last on your nails as long as or longer than polish does on acrylics.
customer_reviews.author: Aalea1

customer_reviews.title: Not a subdued rose pink..... a bit loud...a summer beach pink
customer_reviews.text: This is VERY pink...a summer kind of pink. Not a rose. Shouts a bit more. Do like it only requires one coat. I use Nailtiques Protein Formula 2 Plus on top once or twice a week.
customer_reviews.author: MaryMaryDallasMary

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: Lasts longer than my regular polish and I am really tough on my hands.
customer_reviews.author: mgb411

customer_reviews.title: Very thick
customer_reviews.text: I feel this was so old and so very thick it was almost impossible to use.
customer_reviews.author: donna star

customer_reviews.title: Nailtiques Protein Nail Lacquer in Maui- Works Wonderfully!
customer_reviews.text: I manicure my natural nails every week. Consequently, I have been experimenting with various nail polish lines. I tried Nailtiques Protein Nail Lacquer and I was very pleased with it. Other than normal tip wear, the color adheres very well to my nails for the entire week. I used the Nailtiques color in combination with Nailtiques Protein Formula 1, which I use for my top and base coats. Great combination. I also use Burt's Bees Lemon Butter on my cuticles. My nails look healthy and beautiful. I would strongly recommend these products.
customer_reviews.author: P. J. Turner

customer_reviews.title: Love it!
customer_reviews.text: Best my nails have looked in ages. Polish usually lasts a full week with occasional mini-touch ups.
customer_reviews.author: Nan Carolina

customer_reviews.title: Great for my nails!
customer_reviews.text: This is an excellent nail formula. It's making my nails stronger, healthier and look nice.
customer_reviews.author: Nina Klein

customer_reviews.title: Very disappointed
customer_reviews.text: Product was clumpy and way too thick. Went on thick and glommy. I will not use again. I'm not sure if all similar products will be the same or if it was like that due to the top being slightly open and some spilled out when I received it. Either way due to the bad experience I will never purchase again. Very disappointed
customer_reviews.author: Jenn

customer_reviews.title: My nails are growing very well since I've been using ...
customer_reviews.text: My nails are growing very well since I've been using the nailtiques polish. This color is very soft and natural looking.
customer_reviews.author: Jerry Allgood

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: Item was as described. Arrived on time. We will see if it works as promised.
customer_reviews.author: Casual Shopper

customer_reviews.title: Disappointed in Product
customer_reviews.text: Very difficult to apply with the brush it comes with. Also, does not dry well, even after a long period of time and making sure it was a light coat of polish.
customer_reviews.author: Genelle Parrish

customer_reviews.title: poor condition
customer_reviews.text: Product arrived with polish seeping out from the lid. I returned it, was given another, and the same thing happened. Very disappointed.
customer_reviews.author: genes

customer_reviews.title: LOVE THE COLOR
customer_reviews.text: I love Nailtiques, it is really helping my nails get longer and stronger. The color was exactly what I expected. I will definitely order more colors.
customer_reviews.author: Anne F

customer_reviews.title: Two Stars
customer_reviews.text: just not a fan of how it applies too strike
customer_reviews.author: Barbara I.

customer_reviews.title: If using for french manicure I would reconsider.  Beautiful color.  May need some thinning when purchased through Amazon.
customer_reviews.text: I used Nailtiques thinner when I got this due to reviews and the texture of it when I got it. I was able to get one consistent coat on each nail without a problem. I did want to use this for french manicures but I think this color is a little too opaque for what I was looking for even with one coat, after using thinner in it. You could see the french tip but not nearly as well as I would have liked!!! I used bright white for the tips so that wasn't the problem. It would be beautiful on it's own if that is what you were going for but that isn't my thing.
customer_reviews.author: Deb from Philly

customer_reviews.title: I like this neutral color but the last three bottles I've ...
customer_reviews.text: I use Nailtiques Formula 2 nail protein and, if/when I wish to use nail color with it, I have to order the polish because it is not sold in local stores. I like this neutral color but the last three bottles I've purchased have had a defective cap. When I attempt to open it, only the lid comes off, leaving the actual cap and brush in the bottle. It takes several tries to get the cap to stay within the lid so the bottle can be opened. The polish itself does not chip on my nails.
customer_reviews.author: Barbara J Buck

customer_reviews.title: Three Stars
customer_reviews.text: I get the product broke what can I do? please see picture
customer_reviews.author: Salomon Sutton

customer_reviews.title: Pretty Shade of Polish!
customer_reviews.text: I love Nailtiques products and I wanted to try one of their brighter shades in a red tone. This color, "Maui", is a bright shade of pink. It looked more red in the photo than it actually is. It is a pretty pink, though.
customer_reviews.author: leeway

customer_reviews.title: Good product
customer_reviews.text: While I love the color that I got, it was not the color I expected. I ordered Tahiti & expected it to be a pinkish red but it is really just a dark pink. My only other complaint is that the polish doesn't really hold up very well. I find my polish usually peels or chips after only a day of wear & I only use it with the nailtiques base & top coats. Maybe I just got a bad bottle. Either way, I am a huge fan of nailtiques & will continue to use the product because of the miracles it has worked on my nails.
customer_reviews.author: ooawsom

customer_reviews.title: Perfect Pale Shade of Nail Polish!
customer_reviews.text: I love Nailtiques products, and this lovely shade, "San Tropez", was exactly what I wanted! It's a very pale, subtle color, almost clear but with a hint of barely-there pink.
customer_reviews.author: leeway

customer_reviews.title: Not that great.
customer_reviews.text: The color is obnoxious. Its not quite red, and not quite orange. Its like a really bright coral. Ick. It chips within 10 hours of wear, even with two coats.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Love this product
customer_reviews.text: San tropez is perfect pale color. Love that it's nailtiques and is hardening my nails at the same time. I went back and ordered four more colors it's such a great product. Seems to wear very well too.
customer_reviews.author: Tamiinohio

customer_reviews.title: One Star
customer_reviews.text: Not as pictured. It is off-white. No response to my complaint.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer
